title: For Sale/Trade:  brit .303 no4 mk2 rifle
postcontent:
Manufactured by Fazakerley ( F ) - the finish is original, a type of baked on paint system that was invented by the British - other times known as Suncorite. According to website, the No4 Mk II (or Mk2) was adopted in 1949, with production at ROF-Fazakerley in July, 1949 until 1955. Fazakerley was the only plant to manufacture the No4 Mk2. fairly rare specimen and one to be proud of. The biggest difference in the MK2 and the MK1 is that the trigger of the MK2 is pinned to the receiver instead of the trigger guard. 
Good metal no rust, beautiful wood, original butt plate. Good strong bore. Nice specimen
Mounted is a no drill scope mount with simmons scope and weaver rings.
